      "marks": 2,
      "stimulus": null,
      "content": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Solve the differential equation $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 2y + 5$, given that $y(-2) = 3$. Express your solution as a function of $x$."
        }
      ],
      "parts": null,
      "options": null,
      "answer": {
        "option_label": null,
        "summary": "$y = -\\frac{5}{2} + \\frac{11}{2}e^{2(x+2)}$",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "text": "Separate variables: $\\frac{dy}{2y+5} = dx$. Integrate: $\\frac{1}{2}\\ln|2y+5| = x + C$. Use initial condition to find $C = \\ln\\left(\\frac{11}{2}\\right) - 2$. Solve for $y$ to get $y = -\\frac{5}{2} + \\frac{11}{2}e^{2(x+2)}$."
          }
        ],
        "alternatives": null
      },
      "difficulty": null,
      "topics": ["Differential Equations"],
      "syllabus_points": [],
      "outcomes": [],
      "rubric": null,
      "guidelines": null,
      "created_at": "2026-06-16T02:44:43.568005Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-16T02:44:43.568005Z",
      "source_paper_id": null,
      "source_question_id": null,
      "source_removed": false,
      "remixed_from": null
    },
    {
      "id": "d0e1f2a3-b4c5-46d7-e8f9-a0b1c2d3e4f5",
      "paper_id": "d76b0a8e-7375-4ff8-8540-0377de77d360",
      "author_id": "1",
      "number": 3,
      "type": "long_answer",
      "marks": 6,
      "stimulus": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "The rate of growth of the population of fish in a pond can be described by the differential equation $\\frac{dp}{dt} = 0.2p\\left(\\frac{P - p}{P}\\right)$ where $t$ is the time in months, $p$ is the current population and $P$ is the carrying capacity of the pond."
        }
      ],
      "content": null,
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Show that $\\frac{P}{p(P - p)} = \\frac{1}{p} + \\frac{1}{P - p}$."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 1,
          "is_independent": true,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$\\frac{P}{p(P - p)} = \\frac{1}{p} + \\frac{1}{P - p}$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Partial fractions: $\\frac{P}{p(P - p)} = P\\left(\\frac{A}{p} + \\frac{B}{P - p}\\right)$. Solve for $A$ and $B$ to get $A = \\frac{1}{P}$ and $B = \\frac{1}{P}$. Thus, $\\frac{P}{p(P - p)} = \\frac{1}{p} + \\frac{1}{P - p}$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Hence solve the differential equation, given that there were 100 fish in the pond at the start."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 3,
          "is_independent": false,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$p = \\frac{P}{1 + 4e^{-0.2Pt}}$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Separate variables and integrate using the result from part (a). Use initial condition $p(0) = 100$ to find the constant. The solution is $p = \\frac{P}{1 + 4e^{-0.2Pt}}$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "c",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Given that the population of the fish grew to 250 after 5 months, what is the carrying capacity of the pond?"
            }
          ],
          "marks": 2,
          "is_independent": false,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$P = 500$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Substitute $p(5) = 250$ into the solution from part (b). Solve for $P$ to get $P = 500$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": null,
      "answer": null,
