        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Find the particular solution to the differential equation $(e^{x}+1)\\frac{dy}{dx}=e^{x}\\sec y$ that passes through the origin."
        }
      ],
      "parts": null,
      "options": null,
      "answer": {
        "option_label": null,
        "summary": "$y = \\sin^{-1}\\left(\\frac{e^x}{e^x + 1}\\right)$",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "text": "Separate variables: $\\cos y \\, dy = \\frac{e^x}{e^x + 1} \\, dx$. Integrate: $\\sin y = \\ln(e^x + 1) + C$. Use initial condition $y(0) = 0$ to find $C = 0$. Thus, $y = \\sin^{-1}\\left(\\frac{e^x}{e^x + 1}\\right)$."
          }
        ],
        "alternatives": null
      },
      "difficulty": null,
      "topics": ["Differential Equations"],
