        {
          "kind": "text",
          "text": "Find $I = \\int \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{1 - 9x^2}} \\, dx$."
        }
      ],
      "parts": null,
      "options": null,
      "answer": {
        "option_label": null,
        "summary": "$I = \\frac{2}{3}\\sin^{-1}(3x) + C$",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "text": "Simplify the integrand: $\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{1 - 9x^2}} = \\frac{2}{\\sqrt{1 - 9x^2}}$. Let $u = 3x$, $du = 3\\,dx$. Thus, $I = \\frac{2}{3}\\sin^{-1}(3x) + C$."
          }
        ],
