          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Show that $\\sin 3\\theta + \\sin \\theta = 2\\sin 2\\theta \\cos \\theta$."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 1,
          "is_independent": true,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$\\sin 3\\theta + \\sin \\theta = 2\\sin 2\\theta \\cos \\theta$ using sum-to-product identities.",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Use sum-to-product identity: $\\sin A + \\sin B = 2 \\sin \\left(\\frac{A+B}{2}\\right) \\cos \\left(\\frac{A-B}{2}\\right)$. Thus, $\\sin 3\\theta + \\sin \\theta = 2\\sin 2\\theta \\cos \\theta$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Hence, solve the equation $\\sin 3\\theta + \\sin \\theta = 0$ for $0 \\leq \\theta \\leq 2\\pi$."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 2,
          "is_independent": false,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$\\theta = 0, \\frac{\\pi}{2}, \\pi, \\frac{3\\pi}{2}, 2\\pi$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "From part (a), $2\\sin 2\\theta \\cos \\theta = 0$. Solutions: $\\sin 2\\theta = 0$ or $\\cos \\theta = 0$. For $0 \\leq \\theta \\leq 2\\pi$, $\\theta = 0, \\frac{\\pi}{2}, \\pi, \\frac{3\\pi}{2}, 2\\pi$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": null,
