      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Convert $\\sqrt{3}\\sin x + 3\\cos x$ into the appropriate auxiliary angle form."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 2,
          "is_independent": true,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$2\\sqrt{3}\\sin\\left(x + \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right)$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Express as $R\\sin(x + \\alpha)$. $R = \\sqrt{(\\sqrt{3})^2 + 3^2} = 2\\sqrt{3}$, $\\alpha = \\frac{\\pi}{3}$. Thus, $\\sqrt{3}\\sin x + 3\\cos x = 2\\sqrt{3}\\sin\\left(x + \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right)$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "stimulus": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Hence or otherwise, solve the equation $\\sqrt{3}\\sin x + 3\\cos x = \\sqrt{3}$ for $0 \\leq x \\leq 2\\pi$."
            }
          ],
          "marks": 2,
          "is_independent": false,
          "answer": {
            "option_label": null,
            "summary": "$x = \\frac{2\\pi}{3}, \\frac{4\\pi}{3}$",
            "content": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "From part (a), $2\\sqrt{3}\\sin\\left(x + \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right) = \\sqrt{3}$. Thus, $\\sin\\left(x + \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right) = \\frac{1}{2}$. Solutions: $x + \\frac{\\pi}{3} = \\frac{\\pi}{6} + 2k\\pi$ or $x + \\frac{\\pi}{3} = \\frac{5\\pi}{6} + 2k\\pi$. For $0 \\leq x \\leq 2\\pi$, $x = \\frac{2\\pi}{3}, \\frac{4\\pi}{3}$."
              }
            ],
            "alternatives": null
          }
        }
      ],
      "options": null,
